      <div id="motivation-and-technical-gaps">
        <h3> 1.1 Motivations and Technical Gaps</h3>
        <p>
          Create an optimal scalable CSP test rig with unit measurement (1x1m) for <i>[value proposition]</i>. This value proposition includes talking about free sunlight, cost limitations, why scalable unit, why not PV panels (bc have limited warranty and can degrade). Mention about issue of CSP rig (mirror can crack, maybe to replace with slot for mirror?), and compare with other methods and justify why its better for the industry partner.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div id="aims">
        <h3> 1.2 Aims</h3>
        <p>
          The aim of this project is to improve the existing scalable unit measurement CSP system by improving the receiver component and integrating a thermal energy storage (TES) system to store the collected energy.
          To meet the intended purpose of the prototype, a hot water storage system is to be implemented using the TES system as a heat source.
        </p>
        <p>
          Optimise the test rig using: materials, and mechanical design -> to solve problem of eg. hot water in Indonesia
        </p>
      </div>

